The paper focuses on the design of incentives for human computation systems, which is a topic that falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also uses mechanism design to analyze different incentives, which is a topic that falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) in HCSs, as well as the use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) to improve the efficiency of HCSs. Finally, the paper discusses the ethical and social implications of HCSs, which is a topic that falls under the category of cybernetics (cs.CY).
